{"key":"processedPost-11624479","value":{"id":11624479,"first":11623572,"last":11624704,"when":1260487011,"utime":"12/11/09 01:16 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>prismism said:</b><br />you have become confused about pint cakes. bigger cakes perform <i>better</i> than their smaller counterparts. the only reason people bad mouth pint sized jars for pf tek is because they are harder to get fully colonized.<br />the criticism has nothing to do with the fruiting stage.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Actually, that's not been the experience of most people.&nbsp; Pint cakes rarely fruit as well as half-pint cakes, and certainly not twice as well.&nbsp; They have a higher rate of contamination, and often don't finish colonizing.<br /><br />Using pints isn't a guarantee of failure, but success rates are much higher with smaller cakes.&nbsp; Many growers stack two half-pint cakes on top of each other with a verm layer between them.&nbsp; These perform great and much better than pints, even though they're essentially pint cakes once stacked.<br />RR","title":"Re: My pint cakes are nearly ready to be birthed and I have questions","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}